         <a href="#" class="readMore">Budgeting with M&amp;Ms - Grades 3-8</a>
         <div class="more">
          During this workshop participants will get to experience a hands-on budget lesson that uses multiplication, addition, and subtraction. This lesson will introduce students to budgeting concepts like income and expenses, and the importance of using a budget. During the activity M&amp;Ms are used to represent income and expenses. Students are encouraged to have money left over at the end of the activity. Participants will receive a copy of the lesson plan and a sample package of the budgeting activity that can be reproduced over and over again. This lesson plan can be used for grades 4 and up, and covers Virginia SOLs 4.4b, 5.4, and 6.3.
          <div>
           <br>This workshop covers mathematics for teachers with students in grades 3-8.
          </div>
          <p>Instructor: &nbsp;Sarah Landram, Community Financial Educator, DuPont Community Credit Union</p>
