           <p>Sarah Landram is the Community Financial Educator at DuPont Community Credit Union. In her role as educator, she works with local schools, and other organizations to bring financial education lessons to much of the Central Shenandoah Valley. In 2012, she became a Certified Financial Counselor through the Credit Union National Association’s FiCep program. She is a 2012 graduate of the Harrisonburg-Rockingham Leadership program and a two time winner of the Desjardin Youth Financial Education Award for the state of Virginia. Sarah is also a certified trainer for the National Endowment for Financial Education. Prior to joining the Financial Education department, Sarah worked for 17 years in the Retail area at DCCU.&nbsp;</p>
