         <a href="#" class="readMore">Niche Bots - Grades 3-4</a>
         <div class="more">
          In this hand's-on workshop, participants will construct a Niche-bot that contains a working circuit. The bot must represent its niche, have adaptations for its habitat, and characteristics of its animal type. The bot must include a working pager motor and move independently. Participants will create a unique name for each Niche-bot and design a trading card using appropriate iPad apps. As a group, we will use the trading cards to discuss each Niche-bot’s role in the food web. Target Virginia SOL Standards: Science 3.4, 3.5, 3.6, 4.5, 4.3; English 3.9, 3.10, 3.12, 4.7, 4.8; Math 3.9, 4.6, 4.7; C/T 3-5.2; C/T 3-5.10; C/T 3-5.11 Supporting Virginia SOL Standards: C/T 3-5.
          <div>
           &nbsp;
          </div>
