         <a href="#" class="readMore">Putting the "T" in STEM Learning - Grades 3-8</a>
         <div class="more">
          <blockquote></blockquote>
          <p>Are you overwhelmed with the idea of integrating STEM tools in the classroom? Do you need help determining what tool would be the best fit for you and your students? Is cost the factor? Grade appropriateness? Subject area? Or maybe you need ideas on how integrate tools into your curriculum needs? Come learn and experience 5 STEM learning tools and how they can facilitate interdisciplinary classroom experiences including a hands-on showcase of Squishy Circuits, Makey Makey, Finch Robot, Hummingbird Robotics, and LilyPad Arduino. The presenters will share these tools and the research gained from using them in the classroom, as well as share some of the challenges and successes with implementations. Attendees will get the opportunity to see example projects, learn about ways they have been integrated into multiple subject areas and SOLs, and ignite an interest in utilizing these tools into their own classrooms. In addition to the showcasing of 5 STEM learning tools, the presenters will share additional STEM tools that could be used in the classroom. Although part of the workshop will be lecture, there will be time to explore the tools and projects, ask questions, and brainstorm with the other attendees.<br><br>This workshop covers technology for teachers with students in grades 3-8.</p>
